=== Noun ===
'''mile''' (plural: [[miles]])

# A unit of measure (length or distance) equal to 5,280 [[feet]] in the Customary/[[Imperial]] system of measurements. One mile is equal to 1.609344 [[kilometer]]s.
# A Roman unit of measure equal to about 1620 yards or 1481m.
# A track race of one mile in length; sometimes used to refer to the 1500m race.
#:''The runners completed in the mile.''
# ''slang'' A great distance.
#:''The shot missed by a mile.''

